<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F78E8F7D0269FF785" bold="true" box="[189,453,2066,2092]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
— 
<materialsCitation id="B78E3CD00B7E164E79B7F7D023F3FF75" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3746876332" collectionCode="S, LD, LP, NY" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="120" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" specimenCode="S 14-46283" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="syntype">
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7E164F79B7F7D025D3F785" author="Ekman, E. L." box="[482,649,2066,2092]" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref18616" refString="Ekman, E. L. (1910) Beitrage zur Columniferenflora von Misiones. Arkiv for Botanik 9: 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1910">Ekman (1910)</bibRefCitation>
designated the collection Ekman 145 as type from 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7E164F7D57F7D022FFF785" authorityName="Ekman" authorityYear="1910" box="[1282,1445,2066,2092]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="14" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anarthra">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7E164F7D57F7D022FFF785" box="[1282,1445,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="119">Sida anarthra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, there are 
<specimenCount id="11E0FD040B7F164E793AFF5C2541FF11" box="[367,539,158,184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="generic">five specimens</specimenCount>
of this collection, all 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7F164E7B77FF5D24DDFF10" box="[802,903,159,185]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">syntypes</typeStatus>
, deposited in herbaria 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B7F164E7CC6FF5C23FEFF11" box="[1171,1188,158,184]" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="Herbarium">S</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B7F164E7CE0FF5D2387FF10" box="[1205,1245,159,185]" country="Sweden" name="Lund University" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="Herbarium">LD</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B7F164E7CB9FF5D2256FF10" box="[1260,1292,159,185]" country="Russia" name="Laboratory of Palaeontology" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">LP</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="61F7AE480B7F164E7D1FFF5D2229FF10" box="[1354,1395,159,185]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
. The specimen 
<specimenCode id="57409EF60B7F164E78ACFF002621FF75" box="[249,379,194,220]" collectionCode="S" country="Sweden" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15668" name="Department of Botany, Swedish Museum of Natural History" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="Herbarium">S 14-46283</specimenCode>
was designated as a 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7F164E7A30FF002595FF75" box="[613,719,194,220]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">lectotype</typeStatus>
, because it is representative of the species
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7F164E78E8FF242211FE1D" blockId="15.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E78E8FF2426D4FEA9" bold="true" box="[189,398,230,256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
—According to the description of sections of 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7F164E7BDCFF2424E1FEA9" box="[905,955,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E7BDCFF2424E1FEA9" box="[905,955,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Sida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7F164E7BA8FF2423C5FEA8" author="Fryxell, P. A." box="[1021,1183,230,257]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" pagination="62 - 91" refId="ref18743" refString="Fryxell, P. A. (1985) The North and Central American species of Sida. Sida, Contributions to Botany 11: 62 - 91." type="journal article" year="1985">Fryxell (1985)</bibRefCitation>
we included the species in section 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7F164E7957FEC8261AFE8D" box="[258,320,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Sidae">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E7957FEC8261AFE8D" box="[258,320,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Sidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaves basally entire and distally dentate (dentate almost to the base in this species), base cuneate, sometimes more or less rhomboid, and number of mericarps 7–11 (
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7F164E7B8BFEEC2368FEE1" box="[990,1074,302,328]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Striking features of this species are leaves dentate almost to the base, blades generally narrowly elliptic, narrowly oblong or oblong, abaxial surface tomentose, with margins coarsely serrate; corolla dark yellow, and mericarps with long aristae, greater than 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7F164E7D61FEB4222EFE38" box="[1332,1396,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7F164E78C5FE58266AFE1D" box="[144,304,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="16.[136,229,1921,1943]" captionTargetBox="[222,1366,281,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-66@16.[222,1366,281,1896]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 7. A–E. Sida potentilloides. A. Flower. Adaxial surface of leaf. C. Abaxial surface of leaf. D. Branch with leaves, immature schizocarps and flower bud. E. Branch with leaves and mature schizocarps. F–J. Sida ramoniana. F. Abaxial surface of leaf indument. G. Calyx basis indument tomentose. H. Stem indument pubescent. I. Margin of leaf dentate-crenate. J–O. Sida reitzii. J. Habit. K. Schizocarps in terminal glomerules. L. Adaxial surface of leaf. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Flower. O. Branch. Photographs A–I by Martin Grings (F–J from K. Hagelund 2228, HAS) and J–O by Luís Funez." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415503/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Figures 7A–E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7F164E7969FE58262EFE1D" box="[316,372,410,436]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">14M</figureCitation>
). In the present work, photos of the species in its habitat are presented for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7F164E78E8FE7C2397FDC1" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7F164E78E8FE7C2397FDC1" blockId="15.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E78E8FE7C25BCFE71" bold="true" box="[189,742,446,472]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7F164E7B57FE7C248FFE71" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" box="[770,981,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="potentilloides">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E7B57FE7C248FFE71" box="[770,981,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Sida potentilloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7F164E7C05FE7D23E3FE70" box="[1104,1209,447,473]" name="Paraguay" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7F164E7C90FE7C226DFE71" box="[1221,1335,446,472]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7F164E7D11FE7D22FDFE70" box="[1348,1447,447,473]" name="Uruguay" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
, and in southeast, and south of 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7F164E79B2FE202571FE55" box="[487,555,482,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7F164E7A69FE20247AFE55" author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[572,800,482,508]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7F164E7AF7FE212586FE55" box="[674,732,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7F164E7B78FE2024E5FE55" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[813,959,482,508]" pageId="15" pageNumber="120" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In state of 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7F164E7C05FE20227CFE55" box="[1104,1318,482,508]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
the species grows generally in Araucaria Forest, sometimes associated with Highland grassland, but also in Inland subtropical Forest and Bush grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7F164E79EEFDE82546FDEC" box="[443,540,554,581]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="12.[136,229,2030,2052]" captionTargetBox="[315,1294,482,1962]" captionTargetId="figure-118@12.[258,1329,425,2006]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. Distribution map of Sida glaziovii, S. paradoxa, S. linifolia, S. nemorensis, S. planicaulis, S. potentilloides and S. rubifolia in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415497/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="120">Figure 5</figureCitation>
), in edges of Forests, in ruderal environments and shrubland. The species is Least Concern (LC) because it has large EOO and AOO, since it is a frequent and often ruderal species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
